Hinsdale March 4th 1931
Call her the first part of next week April 6
Yes collect Friday
Dear Mrs. Leitner
I didn't know if I told you that I went to Calif instead of to Florida as I first planned. I do not know exactly when I will be back as I am doing some work in Pasadena. It may be too late to attend myself to sending some work for your members exhibition. Will you be kind enough to let me know now the date and to send me entry blanks here, or you may perhaps fill them out for me. I don't remember whether you said by the of March or April. I asked Mrs. Morris Vehan? to let me have their little boys portrait and she said yes, but I have written them about it and had no answer. Would you be kind enough to call her up and find out if she is away or not and if I can have

element_texts.text: Completed

the picture? I get all your cards sent out here and am sorry I miss so much, but I cannot unfortunately be both places. I love it out here and the weather is perfect. I hear tho that Chicago weather is wonderful also this year. I am only painting a pastel here but may get others. Will not wait for them tho, as I want to visit San Fransisco and Seattle where I have many friends. I hope you are well and happy. Please forgive me for the bother of calling Mrs. Vehan?, but I should be very grateful to you for doing so. I had about 20 letters to write so I cannot tell you much. I go around with a bad conscience all the time, so today I have made up my mind to answer the most important. Morris Vehan?, Jr
Sincerely yours Carol? unclear 627 E. Windsor Road Glendale, Calif 
Mr Morris Vehan Superior 3694 - Portrait of - Vehon?
